{"key":"processedPost-10933413","value":{"id":10933413,"first":10933308,"last":10934075,"when":1251219128,"utime":"08/25/09 07:52 PM","content":"The ebb and flow of substrate moisture content is the number 1 pinning trigger.&nbsp; That's why I also sometimes say it as 'fresh air exchange' is the number one pinning trigger.&nbsp; You want your substrate to evaporate moisture, an then get it partially replaced by misting.&nbsp; After a flush, you've lost perhaps 70 to 90 grams of water(for a brf cake) and that is hard to replace by misting.&nbsp; Misting replaces what evaporates, and dunking replaces what is used by the mushrooms themselves, which are 90% water.<br />RR","title":"Re: Can't water my reservoir"}}